#read in excel file
library(readxl)
energy = read_excel("2_Energy_Consumption.xlsx")
#remove any rows with NA values
energy = na.omit(energy)
#remove comments at end of dataset
energy = energy[0:51,]
#change column names
colnames(energy)=c("State", "Natural Gas", "Distillate Fuel", "Jet Fuel", "Motor Gasoline", "Residual Fuel", "Other", "Total Petroleum", "Ethanol", "Electricity", "Net Energy", "Electrical System Energy Loss", "Total")
library(reshape)
#select subset of variables to work with
energy1=energy[,c("State", "Natural Gas", "Distillate Fuel", "Jet Fuel", "Motor Gasoline", "Residual Fuel", "Other", "Ethanol")]
#convert from table to dataframe
energy1=as.data.frame(energy1)
#change states to abbreviations
energy1$State=state.abb[match(energy1$State,state.name)]
#since DC is the only one without a match, can use that to set DC
energy1$State[is.na(energy1$State)]="DC"
#reorder alphabetically
energy1=energy1[order(energy1$State),]
#create list for visualization of variables by state
df = melt(energy1, id.vars = "State")
library(scales)
library(grDevices)
library(ggplot2)

#set colors using CO2 emissions transformed so that the darker the shade the higher the value, while maintaining relative differences in value (other is aviation gasoline, lubricants and LPG, which is a mix of propane/butane, therefore color set using average of 3)
valcol=c((1-.5307^2), (1-.7315^2), (1-.709^2), (1-.713^2), (1-.7879^2), (1-.6914^2), (1-.2703^2))

#plot stacked barchart for all fuel types as percentage as whole per state
ggplot(df, aes(State, value, fill = variable)) + geom_col(position = "stack", width = 0.75) + scale_fill_manual(values = rgb(valcol, 0, 0)) + labs(fill = "Fuel Type", y = "Trillion Btu", title="State Fuel Breakdowns") + theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12), axis.title=element_text(size=14,face="bold"), title=element_text(size=18,face="bold"))

ggsave("fuel.png", width = 25, height = 10, limitsize=FALSE)
#Group states by US Regions
energy2=energy1
energy2$State=sub("ME|NH|VT|MA|RI|CT|NY|NJ|PA", "Northeast", energy2$State)
energy2$State=sub("OH|MI|IN|WI|IL|MN|IA|MO|ND|SD|NE|KS", "Midwest", energy2$State)
energy2$State=sub("DE|MD|VA|WV|KY|NC|SC|TN|GA|FL|AL|MS|AR|LA|TX|OK|DC", "South", energy2$State)
energy2$State=sub("MT|ID|WY|CO|NM|AZ|UT|NV|CA|OR|WA|AK|HI", "West", energy2$State)
#create list for visualization of variables by state
df2 = melt(energy2, id.vars = "State")
#combine each listing of Region and variable
df2=aggregate(value~State+variable, data=df2, FUN=sum)
#plot stacked barchart for all fuel types as percentage as whole per state
ggplot(df2, aes(State, value, fill = variable)) + geom_col(position = "stack", width = 0.75) + scale_fill_manual(values = rgb(valcol, 0, 0)) + labs(fill = "Fuel Type", y = "Trillion Btu", title="Regional Fuel Breakdowns") + theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12), axis.title=element_text(size=14,face="bold"), title=element_text(size=18,face="bold")) + coord_polar()

ggsave("fuel2.png",width = 10, height = 10, limitsize=FALSE)
